{"name":"For to Summon up a Mighty Wind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a wind that blows out ahead of the caster for as long as he Concentrates on the spell. The wind affects everything within an area 10 metres wide and 20 metres long, in front of the caster&rsquo;s outstretched hand. The wind has increasing effects based on the Magnitude as follows:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 99.1758%; height: 64px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">Magnitude&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Effect</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Candles are blown out.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Ranged attacks at -10%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%; height: 16px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%; height: 16px;\">Birds have trouble flying. Ranged&nbsp;attacks at -20%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Those affected must make an Opposed&nbsp;Athletics roll against the wind&rsquo;s Blowing&nbsp;skill of 50% or fall prone. Ranged attacks&nbsp;at -50%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">As above, but the wind&rsquo;s Blowing skill is 70%. Ranged attacks impossible. Perception at -25% due to flying debris.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Anyone or thing with SIZ less than 21&nbsp;automatically blown over. Perception at&nbsp;-50% due to flying debris.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3458%;\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width: 82.9617%;\">Anyone with SIZ less than 50 flung into&nbsp;the air and suffers 2D6 damage.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0XJBdVctDCnsrlYa"}
{"_id":"0kn3CXHbNgZrlPFd","name":"For the Ignition of the Fires of Passion","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Gives the target the Seduction skill, or adds to the skill if the target already has it, for one single Seduction attempt. At Magnitude 1, this spell gives the target the Seduction skill at base level (INT+CHA), or adds +10% to an existing skill; each increase in Magnitude adds another 10% to the skill. It cannot be stacked with any other spell effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0l8ffj3eXv3RLTam","name":"For the Warming ofthe Mortal Frame","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target suffers no penalties to Fatigue tests from a cold environment while this spell is functioning. Each increase in Magnitude increases the Duration by 10 minutes. The spell also protects the target from one point of cold damage&nbsp; (magickal or mundane) for every point of Magnitude.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"0mK1ThZ3pr4ZcDH3","name":"For the Illumination of the Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a physical object (including living material), this spell causes the object to shed light across a 10 metre area of effect. The area is then considered to be illuminated. Note that only a 10 metre area around the target object is&nbsp; lluminated &ndash; everything outside the area of effect is not. This spell creates raw light, not a flame.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2RzrYRNVpHTMO63p","name":"For to Discover (X)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Element: any</p>\n<p>This covers a family of spells that all operate in a similar fashion, allowing the caster to locate the closest target of the spell within its range. This effect is stopped by a thick substance such as metal, earth or stone that is at least one metre thick. The separate spells For to Discover are listed below and must be learned separately to use them.</p>\n<p>For to Discover an Enemy: Gives the location of the nearest creatures, of a number equal to the Magnitude of the spell, that intend to harm the caster.</p>\n<p>For to Discover Magick: Gives the location and identity of the nearest Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone, magickal potion, or active spell, including Witchcraft. In the case of a Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone, it will tell the caster how many Magick Points it contains.</p>\n<p>For to Discover a (Species): Each For to Discover a (Species) spell will give the location of the nearest creature of the specified species. Examples of this spell include For to Discover a Wolf, For to Discover a Horse and For to Discover a Sparrow.</p>\n<p>For to Discover(Substance): Each spell For to Discover (Substance) will give the location of the nearest substance of the specified type. Examples of this spell include For to Discover Coal, For to Discover Gold and For to Discover Wood.</p>","skill":"Elemental Casting (Air)","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Special","touch":false,"trigger":false,"spellLevel":1},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Drive a Hard Bargain","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target gains a +10% bonus to any Evaluate or Influence test used when evaluating, buying or selling goods or equipment.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4NfUKrn6LB53Dzbx"}
{"_id":"4Ona3YM53EWLUIrm","name":"For to Breathe Like Unto a Dragon","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>With this spell, the caster spits a stream of fire at his target. If the fire is not Dodged, it inflicts 1D8 points of heat damage. Armour Points are effective against this damage and it counts as both magickal and fire damage.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Dodge","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"54926al16bxA6S13","name":"For to Cause the Conflagration of a Blade","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For the Duration, the target weapon will deal 1D10 magickal fire damage on top of its normal damage. A weapon under the effects of For to Cause the Conflagration of a Blade cannot benefit from For to Sharpen a Blade.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":4,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6j4lwA5AWqqSK7Il","name":"For the Encouragement of a Fanatical Mind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target of this spell will have all Close Combat skills increased by +20%, but may not attempt to Parry or cast spells. The target will also have its Dodge skill halved. The effects of this spell are automatically cancelled by the spell For the Invocation of Fear, and vice versa.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to cast a Glamour","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell increases the target&rsquo;s CHA score by +2. A target cannot have its CHA increased in this way to more than twice its original CHA score.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8Q8lEG65xFqedBld"}
{"_id":"8XBEXN4eAeydIJpn","name":"For the Shaping of (an elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GqhGO9h4gSsXkh6Z","name":"For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The caster can summon a lightning bolt from the heavens regardless of the weather. The bolt must strike a target outdoors in plain view. For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue inflicts 3D6 points of damage, ignoring any Armour Points.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Dodge","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the Dismissal of a Salamander","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Kgs822NJn89hWgzZ"}
{"name":"For to Soothe the Restless","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the target to sleep for 10 hours without being disturbed by bad dreams, annoying noises, the pain of wounds, gentle movement and so on. He or she can still be woken by vigorous shaking or a loud noise. The spell does not actually put the target to sleep, merely allows uninterrupted sleep. It is especially useful to help the healing of characters whose Hit Points are currently less than 0.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LCNVz94Li0VEeAdA"}
{"name":"For the Shaping of a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to shape the form of a previously summoned Elemental into any shape he wishes. The Elemental must be controlled within a circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone (see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details). The shape can be anything the caster can imagine, but can never be greater in size than the size in cubic metres of the Elemental summoned. The shaper must be within 5 metres of the Elemental when casting the spell.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LR9g4stS5LLjTqMg"}
