{"name":"For to Dispel a Pestilential Miasma","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell dispels a disease miasma, whether natural or created with the spell For to Create a Pestilential Miasma. The diameter of miasma dispelled is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. If the area dispelled is less than the total area of the miasma, the miasma will contract over the next 1D4 hours, flowing toward its centre so that it remains a continuous area. See Rules and Systems for more details on disease miasmas.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Nh8jMJO2TPARCcCn"}
{"name":"For to Impart Good fortune","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the target to re-roll their next failed skill test. The target can then choose which of the two rolls to use &ndash; so if the target does even worse on the second roll (for instance, getting a fumble where the previous roll was merely a failure) they may choose to keep the first roll. The target can only benefit from one casting of this spell at a time.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"RQBS2pqoP9uppecU"}
{"_id":"StI0qsoakdGTnMDU","name":"For the Summoning of  a Salamander","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Reveal the Secrets of the Heart","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Allows the caster to know which Faction the target belongs to, and gives a measure of the target&rsquo;s Righteousness Points to the nearest 10 RPs (rounded up from the actual figure).</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WpefpcQ9wWTyZAYn"}
{"name":"For the Dismissal of a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"a6k1Fe3RGMnS2GQ0"}
{"name":"For to Meddle with the Fate of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell allows the caster to influence fate, either for the good or ill of the target. The caster can increase or decrease the target&rsquo;s next skill test by 10% for each point of Magnitude. Only the next skill test made after the spell&rsquo;s casting is affected.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aP2EyNuaW50ADWpz"}
{"_id":"bLWDL541nMeGuLDQ","name":"For to Cause the Conflagration of a hurtling Missle","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Casting this spell on a missile weapon, arrow, crossbow bolt, pistol/musket ball or cannonball will cause it to burst into flame when it strikes a target. When it hits a target, the missile will deal 1D10 points of magickal fire damage on top of its normal damage. A missile under the effects of For to Cause the Conflagration of a Hurtling Missile cannot benefit from For to Multiply a Hurtling Missile or For to Speed a Hurtling Missile.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bjqkfAw7T3sz1YmR","name":"For the Dismissal of (an Elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell may be cast against an Elemental of the correct type. It affects an Elemental of up to 1 cubic metre in size per point of Magnitude. Failure to Resist means that the Elemental disperses. It is often difficult to get close to an Elemental in order to dismiss it with this Touch spell. Some solutions to this are discussed in &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"Resilience","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Part the Clouds","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell makes a break in any cloud cover, allowing the sun or moon and stars to shine through. It does not alter the temperature. The diameter of the clear sky is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Any rain, snow, fog, etc. is&nbsp; negated by the spell. The spell effect is centred on the target, and moves with him as he travels. The spell cannot alter magickally-created weather effects of greater Magnitude.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"c1O1QxtYFYJClAGu"}
{"_id":"d2BE5q3sNxQkUkOW","name":"For the Domination of a Familiar(Species)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the caster control over a specific type of non-human creature for the purposes of using it as a Familiar (see the Familiar rules later in this chapter). Each species is a different spell, so<em> For the Domination of a Familiar Dog </em>must be learned separately from<em> For the Domination of a Familiar Cat</em>.</p>\n<p>The caster may attempt to dominate a target of up to 3 INT per 1 Magnitude. If the target fails to Resist, it must obey the caster while the spell lasts.</p>\n<p>The controlled Familiar shares a limited telepathic link with the caster by which it can receive orders; it is completely in thrall to the wishes of the caster and can even be made to take its own life if the caster so wishes. If the Familiar is currently carrying a spell, the spell can be cast with a simple mental command.</p>\n<p>The caster cannot use the senses of the Familiar, so must be able to see the creature if he wants to be sure what it is doing.</p>\n<p>Due to the degree of control exerted on the creature, many Alchemists consider this spell unethical &ndash; it treats an animal as an unfeeling mechanism, something more common among the Mechanical Philosophers of the Parliamentarian cause than anything the average Royalist would espouse.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":true,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Create a Weapon Against Ghosts","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on an item (normally a gun, missile weapon or close combat weapon), this spell allows it to temporarily exist both in the real world and the spirit world. As such, the item can affect ghosts. Damage done to a ghost is taken off its POW; once it&rsquo;s POW&nbsp;reaches zero, the ghost vanishes &ndash; whether it has been</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eMFJ3Buf2BihsHWd"}
{"name":"For to Steady the Hands of a Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell doubles the target&rsquo;s aim bonus the next time they spend (or attempt to spend) at least one round aiming a gun or other ranged weapon, so that aiming for one round will give a +40% bonus, aiming for two rounds will give a +80% bonus, etc. However, if the marksman&rsquo;s aim is interrupted before the shot is fired, the spell&rsquo;s effect is lost.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"hU2uqqT1lDhi9376"}
{"_id":"ikbV7D01vEcCcDC5","name":"For the Ignition of a Consuming Flame","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell will set fire to anything readily flammable within range. Skin or flesh cannot be ignited, and if the target is attached to a living being (such as hair, fur or clothes) then the spell gains the Resist (Resilience) trait.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Fling Far the Hurtling Missile","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a gun, cannon or other ranged weapon, this spell doubles the Range of the weapon for the Duration.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":1,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lL6H6N9ro5tnaJL6"}
{"name":"For to Call the Creative Muse","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell gives the target a +10% bonus per point of Magnitude to his or her next Art skill roll. It cannot stack with any other spell-effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":true},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lSA1jv3weHHcf8ji"}
{"_id":"nu1zf3okpfvlRR36","name":"For to Understand Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude, this spell gives the target +10% to any Language skill he already knows.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the Invocation of a Great Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Light sources within this Area shed no light and normal sight ceases to function. Other senses such as a bat&rsquo;s sonar function normally.</p>","skill":"0","area":5,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oAg1YX4qaqesrEKG"}
{"_id":"pmgK9PUOMwU5Nlk5","name":"For to Count Many Things","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This allows the caster to accurately count a great number of similar things that are together in a mass &ndash; sacks of grain, muskets in an armoury, pikemen in an army. The caster must be able to see what is being counted and very precisely say what he is counting, otherwise the result may not be accurate. For instance, asking for &ldquo;the number of people in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include all the camp-followers, servants, etc., while asking for &ldquo;the number of soldier in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include any prisoners-of-war, and so on.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to See Through the Eyes of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Cast on a living creature (human or animal), this spell allows the caster to see through the eyes of that creature for 5 minutes per point of Magnitude. The caster has no control over what the target looks at, but if the creature has Night Sight, he gains that ability through the eyes of the creature. While this spell is in effect, the caster is blind to anything his own eyes would normally see, but can hear, smell, taste and feel as normal, and can dismiss the spell instantly if he feels the need to see. A target who wants the caster to see through his eyes need not Resist. Familiars that have been calmed with the Lore (Animal) skill or the Dominate Familiar spell will not Resist either.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"Persistence","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qcLbzmc01AE6fOPE"}
{"_id":"tmdsDUaZLRz6ByTf","name":"For to Speak unto the Mind of Another","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell can affect one target for every point of Magnitude. It allows telepathy between the caster and any target, though targets will not have telepathy with one another. The words transmitted by telepathy must be whispered and will be heard directly in the head of the recipient(s), in the same language in which they were spoken.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For to Cause a Person to Speak with Authority","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>For every point of Magnitude of this spell, the target will have +10% added to his Influence skill. The target&rsquo;s voice may also be heard at up to the spell&rsquo;s Magnitude x 100 in metres.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":10,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ttwkQjQQQObbZjNg"}
{"_id":"vjqBGvzPA1MGQVXU","name":"For the Confusion of the Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>If this spell is successful, it garbles the language of the affected person. The target can still think and, for the most part, act normally, but anything it says comes out as gibberish.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vslpS0Tt4b6yDfMa","name":"For the summoning of (an Elemental Type)","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vtrUsbM5QfhnASN6","name":"For the Befuddlement of the Mind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The affected target may not cast spells and may only take non-offensive actions. The target may run if it so chooses and may Dodge and Parry normally in combat, though it may not make any attacks. If the target is directly attacked, the spell is cancelled and the target is free to retaliate.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xi3fKLgIjka6qUEP","name":"For the Invocation of Fear","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target of this spell has all combat skills halved and may not cast offensive spells. If this spell takes effect before combat begins, the target will try to avoid fighting and will either run or surrender. The effects of this spell are&nbsp; automatically cancelled by the spell for the Encouragement of a Fanatical Mind and vice versa.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"For the Summoning of  a Sylph","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell must be learned separately for each of the four types of Elementals described in the Bestiary. The spell summons forth an Elemental of one cubic metre per point of Magnitude, which will manifest after 1D3 combat rounds. There must be enough of the element in question within five metres of the caster when the spell is cast; so a Gnome must be summoned close to Earth (an easy one unless the caster is several stories up in a building or is flying for some reason), a Salamander must be summoned close to a fire big enough to hold its mass, a&nbsp; Sylph must be summoned close to Air (almost anywhere except under water!) and an Undine close to a body of water big enough to hold its mass.</p>\n<p>Note that an Elemental is uncontrolled unless it has been summoned within a&nbsp; circle of powdered Philosopher&rsquo;s Stone &ndash; see &ldquo;Elementals and Their Summoning&rdquo; later in this chapter for details.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":15,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yELyozWTmDcNtu5I"}
{"name":"For the Creation of a Pestilential Miasma","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell creates a disease-causing miasma. The diameter of the miasma is equal to 10 metres per point of Magnitude. Anyone within the miasma must make an opposed Resilience test against the Potency of the disease or immediately&nbsp; contract it (this includes the caster!). Each disease is a different spell, which must be learned separately. See Rules and Systems for more details on disease miasmas.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":24,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":2,"progressive":true,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yZGwXYjzjnEU7jSW"}
